        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer159828910" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8383842874432050902">I chose to switch books by Max Lucado to this one since it is Lent season. The book was very touching and thought evoking - I enjoyed it immensely and recommend it to anyone. The book touches on various aspects of the Crucifixion and really shows how much God loves us to be willing to go through what he did. Although the subject matter is very intense and, heart-rendering, it isn&apos;t a dark book by any stretch. I was nervous about reading it due to the subject matter but Max didn&apos;t focus on the to</span>
  <span id="freeText8383842874432050902" style="display:none">I chose to switch books by Max Lucado to this one since it is Lent season. The book was very touching and thought evoking - I enjoyed it immensely and recommend it to anyone. The book touches on various aspects of the Crucifixion and really shows how much God loves us to be willing to go through what he did. Although the subject matter is very intense and, heart-rendering, it isn't a dark book by any stretch. I was nervous about reading it due to the subject matter but Max didn't focus on the torturous acts more than absolutely necessary to make a point. I haven't been able to watch Mel Gibson's Passion of Christ because of the violence of it - this book doesn't focus on the brutality but rather focuses on God and his reasons for going through the things He did.<br /><br />Max is one of my all-time favorite authors - I haven't read a book by him that I didn't like... at least thus far. :-)</span>
  <a data-text-id="8383842874432050902" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


