<span id="freeTextContainer4166590596013892123">I feel like I&apos;m being generous giving it 3 stars, but I&apos;m biased because I&apos;m frankly Max Lucado&apos;ed out. The first time I read him, easy 4.5 stars, the 2nd one, okay maybe 3.5-4 stars, and this is the 3rd and I want to say 2 stars. But I&apos;ll give it 3 because if I hadn&apos;t read the other 2 that&apos;s what I would possibly give it, but ONLY because I enjoyed the discussion that came out of the book with my Bible study group. I feel like his writing is very repetitive, each of his books is a lot of the sa</span>
  <span id="freeText4166590596013892123" style="display:none">I feel like I'm being generous giving it 3 stars, but I'm biased because I'm frankly Max Lucado'ed out. The first time I read him, easy 4.5 stars, the 2nd one, okay maybe 3.5-4 stars, and this is the 3rd and I want to say 2 stars. But I'll give it 3 because if I hadn't read the other 2 that's what I would possibly give it, but ONLY because I enjoyed the discussion that came out of the book with my Bible study group. I feel like his writing is very repetitive, each of his books is a lot of the same message, and I didn't feel it challenged me as a Christian. It's nice, warm, fuzzy and sentimental, so if that's what you want this will be the book for you. And if you're a huge Lucado fan, you'll love it. But it's my last book of his.</span>
