<div id="review_2763500756" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2763500756" />
    <a title="Hannah H." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40120598-hannah-h"><img alt="Hannah H." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1551051487p2/40120598.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2763500756?book_show_action=true">Apr 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hannah H." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hannah H." href="/user/show/40120598-hannah-h">Hannah H.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2763500756" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13916193682588082858">Lucado does such a good job of weaving truth and story together to create compelling books, especially in audiobook form. While his stuff is never the deepest or most challenging (which is largely why this book didn’t get high marks from me), it never fails to be refreshing. This book in particular helped me see the realness of Jesus in a new way, as Lucado looked at the life and ministry of our Savior as it relates to our humanity. He too, suffered in all the ways we have. What a mind blowing a</span>
  <span id="freeText13916193682588082858" style="display:none">Lucado does such a good job of weaving truth and story together to create compelling books, especially in audiobook form. While his stuff is never the deepest or most challenging (which is largely why this book didn’t get high marks from me), it never fails to be refreshing. This book in particular helped me see the realness of Jesus in a new way, as Lucado looked at the life and ministry of our Savior as it relates to our humanity. He too, suffered in all the ways we have. What a mind blowing and beautiful comfort that is!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13916193682588082858" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


