        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2768029257" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17938668115062960906">I gave this book five stars because out of all the religious books I’m reading this Lent, Max Lucado writes in a way that makes one have no doubt that we are all saved, even though we are all sinners. That doesn’t mean we can go out and do whatever we want. We should treat moments in our lives as ones where Jesus is leading us, and we should put all our trust in Him. If we do, we will all meet one day in Heaven. Jesus has laid out all our sins on the cross and we are forgiven. Jesus chose the na</span>
  <span id="freeText17938668115062960906" style="display:none">I gave this book five stars because out of all the religious books I’m reading this Lent, Max Lucado writes in a way that makes one have no doubt that we are all saved, even though we are all sinners. That doesn’t mean we can go out and do whatever we want. We should treat moments in our lives as ones where Jesus is leading us, and we should put all our trust in Him. If we do, we will all meet one day in Heaven. Jesus has laid out all our sins on the cross and we are forgiven. Jesus chose the nails so He could be with us for eternity! He knows our sins and died for our sins so heaven can be opened for us!<br />I loved how stories of our lives was brought out as examples of how God loves us and our sins are forgiven. This book gives hope. It also has a study guide and questions to ask yourself, and many Bible passages and readings for further study. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17938668115062960906" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
