      <div class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/work/quotes/273545-he-chose-the-nails-what-god-did-to-win-your-heart">Quotes from He Chose the Nail...</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;The same hand that stilled the seas stills your guilt.<br />The same hand that cleansed the Temple cleanses your heart.<br />The hand is the hand of God.<br />The nail is the nail of God.<br />And as the hands of Jesus opened for the nail, the doors of heaven opened for you.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/701176-the-same-hand-that-stilled-the-seas-stills-your-guilt">33 likes</a>
            </nobr>
            <div class="clear"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;But here the correlation with Beauty and the Beast ends. In the fable, the beauty kisses the beast. In the Bible, the beauty does much more. He becomes the beast so the beast can become the beauty. Jesus changes places with us. We, like Adam, were under a curse, but Jesus "changed places with us and put himself under that curse" (Gal. 3:13).&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/813878-but-here-the-correlation-with-beauty-and-the-beast-ends">23 likes</a>
            </nobr>
            <div class="clear"></div>
          </div>
        <a class="actionLink" style="float: right" href="/work/quotes/273545-he-chose-the-nails-what-god-did-to-win-your-heart">More quotes&hellip;</a>
<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

